verbose_text: The SSX family of genes consists of several subtypes Tureci et al. studied the expression of SSX genes in 325 specimens of human neoplasms, and found that SSX-1, -2, and -4 subtypes are expressed in 8%, 15% and 15% of the cancers, respectively, while the expression of the SSX-5 or SSX-3 subtypes were rare or absent.
